<article class="prose">
  <h1>add a word</h1>
  <p>directionary grows one entry at a time. to add a word:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>fork the repository.</li>
    <li>create a new file at <code>src/words/&lt;first-letter&gt;/&lt;word&gt;.md</code>.</li>
    <li>fill in the frontmatter: <code>word</code>, <code>pos</code>, <code>meaning</code> — and optionally <code>pronunciation</code>, <code>example</code>, <code>dateAdded</code>.</li>
    <li>open a pull request.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>template:</p>
  <pre><code>---
word: "Serendipity"
pos: "noun"
pronunciation: "/ˌser.ənˈdɪp.ə.ti/"
meaning: "A pleasant surprise; finding something good without looking for it."
example: "Meeting her was pure serendipity."
dateAdded: "2026-06-21"
---</code></pre>
</article>
